schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1892,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Hash Table","Prefix Sum"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a 2D integer array `ranges` and two integers `left` and `right`. Each `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` represents an **inclusive** interval between `starti` and `endi`.\n\nReturn `true` *if each integer in the inclusive range* `[left, right]` *is covered by **at least one** interval in* `ranges`. Return `false` *otherwise*.\n\nAn integer `x` is covered by an interval `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` if `starti <= x <= endi`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: ranges = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]], left = 2, right = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Every integer between 2 and 5 is covered:\n- 2 is covered by the first range.\n- 3 and 4 are covered by the second range.\n- 5 is covered by the third range.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: ranges = [[1,10],[10,20]], left = 21, right = 21\nOutput: false\nExplanation: 21 is not covered by any range.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= ranges.length <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= starti <= endi <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= left <= right <= 50`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Hash Table","Prefix Sum"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a 2D integer array `ranges` and two integers `left` and `right`. Each `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` represents an **inclusive** interval between `starti` and `endi`.\n\nReturn `true` *if each integer in the inclusive range* `[left, right]` *is covered by **at least one** interval in* `ranges`. Return `false` *otherwise*.\n\nAn integer `x` is covered by an interval `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` if `starti <= x <= endi`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: ranges = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]], left = 2, right = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Every integer between 2 and 5 is covered:\n- 2 is covered by the first range.\n- 3 and 4 are covered by the second range.\n- 5 is covered by the third range.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: ranges = [[1,10],[10,20]], left = 21, right = 21\nOutput: false\nExplanation: 21 is not covered by any range.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= ranges.length <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= starti <= endi <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= left <= right <= 50`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-all-the-integers-in-a-range-are-covered/","problemName":"Check if All the Integers in a Range Are Covered","problemNumber":1893,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a 2D integer array `ranges` and two integers `left` and `right`. Each `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` represents an **inclusive** interval between `starti` and `endi`.\n\nReturn `true` *if each integer in the inclusive range* `[left, right]` *is covered by **at least one** interval in* `ranges`. Return `false` *otherwise*.\n\nAn integer `x` is covered by an interval `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` if `starti <= x <= endi`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: ranges = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]], left = 2, right = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Every integer between 2 and 5 is covered:\n- 2 is covered by the first range.\n- 3 and 4 are covered by the second range.\n- 5 is covered by the third range.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: ranges = [[1,10],[10,20]], left = 21, right = 21\nOutput: false\nExplanation: 21 is not covered by any range.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= ranges.length <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= starti <= endi <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= left <= right <= 50`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Easy","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given a 2D integer array `ranges` and two integers `left` and `right`. Each `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` represents an **inclusive** interval between `starti` and `endi`.\n\nReturn `true` *if each integer in the inclusive range* `[left, right]` *is covered by **at least one** interval in* `ranges`. Return `false` *otherwise*.\n\nAn integer `x` is covered by an interval `ranges[i] = [starti, endi]` if `starti <= x <= endi`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: ranges = [[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]], left = 2, right = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: Every integer between 2 and 5 is covered:\n- 2 is covered by the first range.\n- 3 and 4 are covered by the second range.\n- 5 is covered by the third range.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: ranges = [[1,10],[10,20]], left = 21, right = 21\nOutput: false\nExplanation: 21 is not covered by any range.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= ranges.length <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= starti <= endi <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= left <= right <= 50`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-all-the-integers-in-a-range-are-covered/","problemName":"Check if All the Integers in a Range Are Covered","problemNumber":1893,"problemSlug":"check-if-all-the-integers-in-a-range-are-covered","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1893,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Binary Search","Simulation","Prefix Sum"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There are `n` students in a class numbered from `0` to `n - 1`. The teacher will give each student a problem starting with the student number `0`, then the student number `1`, and so on until the teacher reaches the student number `n - 1`. After that, the teacher will restart the process, starting with the student number `0` again.\n\nYou are given a **0-indexed** integer array `chalk` and an integer `k`. There are initially `k` pieces of chalk. When the student number `i` is given a problem to solve, they will use `chalk[i]` pieces of chalk to solve that problem. However, if the current number of chalk pieces is **strictly